<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="382">Adaskin, Harry, Canadian violinist; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="379" RE="Sept. 17, 1901" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="373" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="303" rule1="GazLocation" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Riga</Location>, <Location gate:gateId="304" rule1="GazLocation" locType="country" rule2="LocFinal">Latvia</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="305" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">Sept. 17, 1901</Date></Event_Birth>. He was brought to <Location gate:gateId="306" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="306;319;322" rule2="LocFinal">Toronto</Location> at the age of two, and studied at the Toronto Cons. (<Date gate:gateId="308" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1912</Date>then entered the Chicago Musical College and later studied in <Location gate:gateId="310" rule1="InLoc1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Paris</Location>. From <Date gate:gateId="311" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1923</Date>he was second violinist of the Hart House String Quartet, which toured in <Location gate:gateId="313" rule1="InLoc1" locType="region" rule2="LocFinal">Europe</Location> and <Location gate:gateId="314" rule1="Location1" locType="country" rule2="LocFinal">America</Location>. In <Date gate:gateId="315" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1946</Date> he was appointed violin teacher at the Univ. of <Location gate:gateId="316" rule1="GazLocation" locType="province" rule2="LocFinal">British Columbia</Location>, <Location gate:gateId="317" rule1="GazLocation" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Vancouver</Location>. His brother, Murray Adaskin (<Event_Birth gate:gateId="380" RE="March 28, 1906" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="374" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="319" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="306;319;322" rule2="LocFinal">Toronto</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="320" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">March 28, 1906</Date></Event_Birth>) is also a violinist; another brother, John Adaskin (<Event_Birth gate:gateId="381" RE="June 4, 1908" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="375" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="322" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="306;319;322" rule2="LocFinal">Toronto</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="323" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">June 4, 1908</Date></Event_Birth>) is a cellist. </paragraph>